debugger-ui-emacs-aldb — Phase 7: Emacs UI (aldb, SLDB-modelled)
================================================================

See also:
  clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-implementation-plan.org (Phase 7)
  clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-spec.org (§20)
  issues/open/debugger-ui-protocol-and-dumb.issue (prerequisite — Phase 5)

Context
-------

The Emacs UI exposes the debugger over a small RPC to an Emacs minor mode,
modelled on SLDB (named `aldb`, as SLIME's debugger is `sldb`). The aim is
parity with SLDB's interactive feel, not its protocol. A feature missing in
the dumb terminal is missing here too (spec §20.4).

Scope / deliverables
--------------------

1. RPC (spec §20.1): line-oriented S-expression messages read with `read`;
   `(<message-tag> <args>...)`. No length prefixes / encoding negotiation /
   Bencode. This same S-expr shape is later reused by the remote-CAD channel.
   New system `clautolisp/autolisp-debug-ui-emacs` for the CL-side shim
   (translates `cmd-*` <-> RPC, surfaces `ui-*` as RPC events).

2. Emacs `clautolisp-debug-mode` / `aldb` (elisp, shipped under the project's
   emacs/ or tools/ tree): buffers `*clautolisp-debug*`, `*clautolisp-bindings*`,
   `*clautolisp-stack*`, `*clautolisp-inspect*`, `*clautolisp-workspace*`, and
   source-buffer overlays at poll points / breakpoints / current form
   (spec §20.2).

3. Keybindings (spec §20.3): c/s/i/o/f/SPC/RET/e/v/b/C-c C-b/d/q mirroring
   SLDB; inspector-buffer bindings RET/TAB/S-TAB/DEL/p/b/B/M-RET/e/v/q
   (spec §20.2), incl. `$path` and "Copy to REPL" (M-RET) idiom.

Acceptance
----------

- SLDB-parity feel for break/step/inspect from Emacs against an in-image
  session; source overlays placed from debug metadata; workspace buffer works.
- `*version*` bumped (CL side); elisp linted/byte-compiled clean.

* Resolution (triage 2026-07-23)

Shipped: autolisp-debug-ui-emacs (socket UI) + emacs/aldb.el (aldb-connect, SLDB-style keymap).
